Question:
Write a program to simulate Stone–Paper–Scissor game.

Rules:

Stone beats Scissor

Scissor beats Paper



Code:


import random

choices = ["stone", "paper", "scissor"]
user = input("Enter your choice (stone/paper/scissor): ").lower()
comp = random.choice(choices)
print("Computer:", comp)

if user == comp:
    print("Result: Draw")
elif (user == "stone" and comp == "scissor") or \
     (user == "scissor" and comp == "paper") or \
     (user == "paper" and comp == "stone"):
    print("Result: You Win!")
else:
    print("Result: You Lose!")


Sample Input / Output:

Enter your choice (stone/paper/scissor): stone
Computer: scissor
Result: You Win!
